content:
After a model is deployed, you can use it to display predictions and improvements for a standard or custom object on a Lightning Experience record page.

To add the Einstein Predictions component to a Lightning page:

Customize Application
View Einstein Discovery Recommendations (see Assign Einstein Discovery Permission Sets to Users)

Drop the Einstein Predictions component where you want it on the Lightning record page.
In the component configuration panel, use the Prediction lookup to find and select the prediction you want to embed in the page.

Optionally, configure other settings:

Prediction: Search for a list of any predictions (deployed models) to which you have access.
Show Prediction Label: Select this check box to show the prediction label.
Title: Descriptive label for the prediction.
Show title: Select this checkbox to show the title.
Prediction score unit:
Unit precedes score: Select this checkbox to show units preceding the prediction.

When a user views this record page, predictions are updated in real time. No writeback to Salesforce is needed.
title: Embedding Predictions on Lightning Pages
